Paul,<br><br>
Take some time, but do come back and say what you feel is important.  It can have surprising effects. <br><br>
I know that we were not there to kill women and children.  I also know it happened.  That's war.  It happened in Poland during WWII too, and everywhere war has occurred.  As a poster in our alert quarters of a flower with all but one pedals having fallen off, and that one just hanging, said, so many years ago, &quot;War is not healthy for children and other living things!&quot;
